The global nursing care market is witnessing robust growth propelled by several key factors. The increasing elderly population, coupled with a rising incidence of chronic ailments, is driving the demand for nursing care services worldwide. Additionally, advancements in healthcare infrastructure and technologies are enhancing the quality of care provided to patients. The market is experiencing a notable shift towards home care services, where patients can receive personalized medical assistance and attention within the comfort of their homes, further boosting market growth.

